## initrd-start

**Value type:** `<u32>` or `<u64>`

Specifies the physical start address of an initial ramdisk (initrd) image loaded by the bootloader. Written by firmware or bootloader before passing control to the kernel. Used together with `linux,initrd-end`.

Note: This property is typically written as `linux,initrd-start` in the `/chosen` node by the bootloader.

```dts
chosen {
    linux,initrd-start = <0x84000000>;
    linux,initrd-end   = <0x84800000>;
};
```
